alerts.title: Winter Weather Advisory
alerts.description: ...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 2 AM TO 8 PM EST SUNDAY... * WHAT... A mixture of snow, sleet and freezing rain will develop by sunrise and last through most of the day tomorrow before changing to a period of snow during the late afternoon and early evening. Ice accumulations may exceed a tenth of an inch with snow and sleet accumulations up to and over an inch in spots. * WHERE...In Pennsylvania, Pike County. In New York, Chenango, Otsego, Delaware and Sullivan Counties. * WHEN...From 2 AM to 8 PM EST Sunday. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... Freezing rain will accumulate on exposed surfaces leading to slippery conditions. Untreated roads will become slick and hazardous as well.
